{
  "stem": "8784.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But we decide to go to a school which was a all-Jewish student body in the city of Krakow, located in the Kazimierz in the middle of the city of Krakow.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This was the- school name was [NON-ENGLISH] on [NON-ENGLISH] Street in Krakow.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My family was religious.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All depends on, on who would say that, because I thought my family was religious, but I-- on the other hand, I know that my grandfather and my uncle would have not eaten in our house because we were not religious enough for, for their standards.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father came from the city of Auschwitz, which was known in Polish as the city of Oswiecim, the later, the later infamous the city of Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother came from Kalwaria-Zebrzydowski.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And as best I understand, this was a matched marriage in those days.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they-- later on, after they got married, they lived in Kalwaria.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We did have some non-Jewish friends.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember more the Jewish friends, because in school, my classmates were all Jewish.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But at home, I would have some non-Jewish friends.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it was a rather difficult situation, because we're speaking about the time of 1933 when I arrived in Poland.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And anti-Semitism, at that time, has reached a high pitch.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "With the coming to the power of Hitler in Germany, the anti-Semitism was sweeping Europe in a big way, particularly Poland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so I remember the unpleasantries that you would have to live with as a Jewish child in a non-Jewish neighborhood where I lived.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was not uncommon for the non-Jewish children to throw stones, rocks, at the, at the Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
